.:: Einstein-puzzle ::.

House: townhouse, cape-cod, tower, wooden, craftsman
There are 5 different nationalities: british, danish, german, norwegian, swede
There are 5 different favourite beverages: beer, coffee, milk, tea, water
5 different brands of cigars are smoked: townhousemaster, dunhill, pall-mall, prince, blend
5 different pets are kept: cat, bird, dog, fish, horse
1. the british is the tower house
2. the swedish is the owner of the dog
3. the danish is the person drinking tea
4. the cape-cod house is on the left of the wooden house
5. the cape-cod house is the person drinking coffee
6. the pall-mall-smoker is the owner of the bird
7. the craftsman house is the dunhill-smoker
8. the person drinking milk is in the middle
9. the norwegian is on the far left
10. the blend-smoker is on the left or right of the owner of the cat
11. the owner of the horses is on the left or right of the dunhill-smoker
12. the townhousemaster-smoker is the person drinking beer
13. the german is the prince-smoker
14. the norwegian is on the left or right of the townhouse house
15. the blend-smoker is on the left or right of the person drinking water

.:: Answer ::.
|		|	1	|	2	|	3	|	4	|	5	|
| House		|    craftsman	|     townhouse	|      tower	|     cape-cod	|     wooden	|
| Nationality	|   norwegian	|    danish	|    british	|    german	|    swedish	|
| Pet		|     cat	|    horse	|     bird	|     fish	|      dog	|
| Beverage	|    water	|     tea	|     milk	|    coffee	|      beer	|
| Cigar		|   dunhill	|    blend	|  pall-mall	|    prince	|   townhousemaster	|
